NOTES FROM SEINEING SEASON:: During several seines throughtout the summer, many YOY clupeid species were caught and difficult to identify. In a lab, one fish was identified as American Shad, the other as Blueback Herring. The two species are very difficult to distinguish unless opened up to observe the peritoneum.                             Species with an astirik * are listed with best educated guess, but not certainty.
